# 6. わからない、本心

Len: <Wow, that's so cool... You really are drawing her.>
Mafuyu: Ena, what sort of expression do you need me to make...?
Ena: Your usual one should be fine.
Mafuyu: Okay.
Ena: (Honestly, I wasn't expecting to actually do a drawing of her...)
Ena: (She's so expressionless... It's like I'm drawing a sculpture.)
Len: <You really are a good artist, Ena...>
Len: <And it's so admirable how you're still trying to get better...>
Ena: I'm not good or anything.
Ena: But I do want to get better.
Ena: To be fair, each day feels like a struggle since no matter how much I draw, I keep getting told how awful my drawings are.
Len: <Ena...>
Ena: But this is what I want to do. This is the path I've chosen.
Ena: I don't care what anyone says. I'm not gonna stop drawing.
Mafuyu: ...
Ena: I know me doing this makes my mom really worried sometimes.
Ena: But I honestly think that doing art is what suits me best.
Mafuyu: What suits you best...?
Ena: Yeah. So, why don't you try telling your mom what you really want to do?
Ena: Including the part about your synth...
Mafuyu: I already told her that I don't want to stop...
Ena: What...?
Mafuyu: I told her that I know that I need to study but also want to keep making music...
Ena: Wait, you did?!
Ena: (She already tried...?)
Mafuyu: And she said that I'm free to do as I wish...
Ena: Really? Then...
Mafuyu: But she also told me to not regret my decision...
Ena: What...?
Mafuyu: She was telling me to think about my future and not make regretful choices...
Ena: Huh? What's she talking about...? Why would you regret making music?
Mafuyu: I don't think that's what she was talking about...
Mafuyu: Knowing her, she was probably more focused on my future...
Mafuyu: By becoming a doctor, I'll be able to help many people and live comfortably...
Ena: Yeah, you're not wrong. But...
Mafuyu: My mom knows that things will become much harder if I don't study and do well on the entrance exams...
Mafuyu: So...
Mafuyu: So... I...
Mafuyu: I said that I'd step away from music...
Ena: ...!
Ena: What?! You actually told her that?!
Mafuyu: Yes...
Ena: And you're really okay with that...? None of this bothers you?
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: If I study and bide my time, by the time I'm in university... I might be able to pick it back up...
Mafuyu: So, for now...
Ena: And yet, you're still here making music with us...
Mafuyu: That's what I still don't understand...
Mafuyu: The other day, Ena, when you said, “You wouldn't be in SEKAI if you thought your mom was right.”
Mafuyu: I agree with you.
Mafuyu: It made me wonder why am I doing the opposite of what my mom is telling me to do...
Ena: Because that's what you wanted to do, right...?
Ena: You want to make music and go to SEKAI. It doesn't matter what she says. You're not willing to give those things up. You want to be a part of N25. Am I wrong?
Ena: It's only natural for you to feel that way.
Mafuyu: It is...?
Ena: Yeah.
Ena: Just look at me. I draw because I want to draw, and I believe I'll be rewarded in the future.
Ena: So, I would think that there's a part of you that knows what would truly make you happy. And it's not what your mom decides...
Mafuyu: What makes me happy...?
Mafuyu: But I...
Len: <Mafuyu...?>
Ena: (This is a tough one...)
Ena: (I get that her mom means a lot to her... But why can't Mafuyu just say what she wants to do.)
Ena: (I mean, based on our conversation, it's clear that her heart lies elsewhere.)
Ena: (Hmm... What if it were me in her shoes? Would things have turned out differently...?)
Ena: (If my parents constantly pushed their ideals onto me because it's “for my sake”...)
Ena: (Would I have turned into Mafuyu...?)
Ena: Let's take your mom out of the equation for a second, Mafuyu. What do you want to do?
Mafuyu: I don't know...
Mafuyu: But I want to make music with all of you...
Ena: Mafuyu...
Ena: Okay...
Ena: Then, as a fellow member of N25, I'll do what I can to help.
Ena: At the same time, “being yourself” is probably easier said than done in your case.
Ena: So, why don't you use today to practice doing just that? It'll be your chance to do whatever you want...
Mafuyu: What...?
Ena: Wait, it's already 25:00?! I need to get to work! I totally lost track of the time while drawing...!
Mafuyu: Work...?
Ena: On N25 stuff! Don't you also have work to do?
Mafuyu: Am I allowed to...?
Ena: Huh? You're kidding, right? Kanade's probably done polishing up her song, which means Mizuki and I need you to finish writing your lyrics.
Ena: Anyway, lemme open up Nightcord.
Mafuyu: Okay...
